Compute Payment to Reach a Financial Goal
The formula used to get the future value of an ordinary annuity is useful, finding out what the final amount in the account will be. However, that isnâ€™t how planning works. To plan, we need to know how much to put into the ordinary annuity each compounding period in order to reach a goal. Fortunately, that formula exists.

FORMULA
The formula for the amount that needs to be deposited per period,  ğ‘ğ‘šğ‘¡
 , of an ordinary annuity to reach a specified goal,  ğ¹ğ‘‰
 , is  ğ‘ğ‘šğ‘¡=ğ¹ğ‘‰Ã—(ğ‘Ÿ/ğ‘›)(1+ğ‘Ÿ/ğ‘›)ğ‘›Ã—ğ‘¡âˆ’1
 , where  ğ‘Ÿ
  is the annual interest rate (in decimal form),  ğ‘›
  is the number of periods per year, and  ğ‘¡
  is the number of years.

With this formula, it is possible to plan the amount to be saved.

